108.7	Eliot_Spitzer	Eliot Spitzer	Eliot Laurence Spitzer (born June 10, 1959) is an American lawyer, political commentator, and former Democratic Party politician. He was the co-host of In the Arena, a talk-show and punditry forum broadcast on CNN from October 2010 to July 2011. He served as the 54th Governor of New York from January 2007 until his resignation on March 17, 2008 in the wake of the exposure of his involvement as a client of Emperors Club VIP. Prior to being elected governor, Spitzer served as New York State Attorney General.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b5/Eliot_Spitzer.jpg/220px-Eliot_Spitzer.jpg
